[2026-03-18T18:45:43.861Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019rNayeDQiCV4g9yReh3JfL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Project Structure\n\nThe personas-cloud repository is organized as a monorepo with three main packages:\n\n- **packages/shared** - Shared types, protocols, and utilities\n- **packages/orchestrator** - Central service coordinating personas, events, and triggers\n- **packages/worker** - Worker nodes executing persona prompts\n- **Root** - Standard monorepo config with npm workspaces\n\n### 2. Trigger System Architecture\n\nThe trigger system follows a **heap-driven scheduler pattern** with in-memory optimization:\n\n#### Key Files:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts` - Main scheduler\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/triggers.ts` - Trigger persistence\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHttpHandlers.ts` - HTTP API handling\n\n#### How Triggers Work:\n\n1. **Startup** (`buildHeap` function):\n   - `startTriggerScheduler()` loads all enabled triggers from all tenant DBs\n   - Populates an in-memory min-heap keyed by `nextTriggerAt` timestamp\n   - Enables O(1) peek for next due trigger\n\n2. **Scheduled Firing** (`tick` function):\n   - Min-delay: 100ms, Max-delay: 60s\n   - On each tick, heap pops due entries (where `nextTriggerAt ≤ now`)\n   - Counts \"missed\" triggers (> 60s late) for observability\n   - Calls `fireDueEntries()` to process them\n\n3. **Fire Process** (`fireDueEntries` function):\n   - Groups due triggers by tenant ID for efficient batch DB queries\n   - Fetches triggers + persona data via `getTriggersByIdsWithPersona()`\n   - Skips triggers for deleted/disabled personas\n   - Publishes `trigger_fired` event via `publishEvent()`\n   - Computes next fire time: `computeNextTriggerAtFromParsed()`\n   - Updates DB with `updateTriggerTimings()` (last_triggered_at, next_trigger_at)\n   - Pushes updated entry back into heap\n   - Logs firing with metrics\n\n4. **Heap Management** (TriggerSchedulerHandle):\n   - `heapPush()` - Add/update trigger in heap\n   - `heapRemove()` - Remove trigger from heap\n   - `nudge()` - Force immediate re-evaluation\n   - `getMetrics()` - Return scheduler observability data\n\n#### Trigger Types (from types.ts):\n- `'manual'` - No automatic firing\n- `'schedule'` - Cron or interval-based (supported: `\"every Xm/h/s/d\"` shorthand or standard cron)\n- `'polling'` - Poll URL at interval\n- `'webhook'` - Receive external triggers\n- `'chain'` - Triggered by events from other personas\n\n### 3. Database Layer\n\n#### Architecture:\n- **Single-database mode** (legacy): Monolithic SQLite with all tenants\n- **Multi-tenant mode** (current): System DB + per-tenant DBs via `TenantDbManager`\n\n#### Key Database Files:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` - Schema definitions\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/index.ts` - Barrel export\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/_helpers.ts` - Utilities (stmt cache, row mappers)\n\n#### Core Tables:\n- `personas` - Persona definitions\n- `persona_triggers` - Trigger definitions (indexed on enabled + next_trigger_at)\n- `persona_events` - Event queue (status: pending, processing, delivered, skipped, failed, partial, partial-retry)\n- `persona_event_subscriptions` - Event listener subscriptions\n- `persona_executions` - Execution history and results\n- `persona_tool_definitions` - Tool definitions\n- `persona_credentials` - Encrypted credentials\n- `inference_profiles` - Model/provider configurations\n\n#### Key Features:\n- **WAL mode** enabled for concurrency\n- **Foreign key constraints** enforced\n- **Prepared statement caching** via `stmt()` helper\n- **Automatic migrations** for schema evolution\n- **Row mapper factory** for type-safe mapping\n\n### 4. HTTP API Routes\n\n#### Files:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` - Main HTTP server\n\n#### Route Structure:\n- **Exact-path routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:/path`)\n  - OAuth, token, status, execute, admin routes\n  - Delegated to specialized handlers\n\n- **Resource routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]`)\n  - Personas CRUD + sub-resources (tools, credentials, subscriptions, triggers)\n  - Events CRUD + webhooks\n  - Subscriptions, Credentials, Executions, Tool-definitions\n\n#### Trigger Routes (via `triggerHttpHandlers.ts`):\n- `POST /api/triggers` - Create trigger → `heapPush()` + `nudge()`\n- `PUT /api/triggers/:id` - Update trigger → update DB + update/remove from heap\n- `DELETE /api/triggers/:id` - Delete trigger → `heapRemove()` + delete DB\n- `GET /api/personas/:id/triggers` - List triggers for persona\n\n#### Key Design Patterns:\n- Route parsing: `/api/{resource}[/{id}[/{subResource}]]`\n- Auth context extraction: admin vs user-scoped access\n- Database routing via `TenantDbManager` for multi-tenant\n- Error handling: 400 (validation), 404 (not found), 409 (conflict), 429 (backpressure), 500 (internal)\n\n### 5. Shared Types\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n\n#### Core Domain Types:\n\n**Persona**:\n- `id`, `projectId`, `name`, `description`, `systemPrompt`\n- `enabled`, `maxConcurrent`, `timeoutMs`\n- `inferenceProfileId`, `networkPolicy`, `maxBudgetUsd`, `maxTurns`\n\n**Events**:\n- `PersonaEvent` - Event record with status state machine\n- Event statuses: `'pending' | 'processing' | 'delivered' | 'skipped' | 'failed' | 'partial' | 'partial-retry'`\n- Legal transitions defined in `EVENT_TRANSITIONS` map\n- `PersonaEventSubscription` - Listener binding persona to event types\n\n**Triggers**:\n- `PersonaTrigger` - Trigger record (id, personaId, triggerType, config, enabled, nextTriggerAt)\n- `TriggerConfig` - Discriminated union of config types\n- `TriggerType` - `'manual' | 'schedule' | 'polling' | 'webhook' | 'chain'`\n\n**Execution**:\n- `PersonaExecution` - Execution record (id, personaId, status, inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd)\n- `ExecRequest` - Request to execute persona\n- `ExecResult` - Completion result\n\n**Credentials**:\n- `PersonaCredential` - Encrypted credential storage (encryptedData, iv, tag)\n- `InferenceProfile` - Model provider configuration\n\n### 6. Protocol Definitions\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts`\n\n#### WebSocket Protocol (dac-wire):\n\n**Worker → Orchestrator**:\n- `hello` - Initial handshake with capabilities\n- `ready` - Worker ready to accept assignments\n- `stdout` / `stderr` - Output chunks\n- `complete` - Execution finished\n- `event` - Custom event emission\n- `progress` - Phase progress (0-100%)\n- `heartbeat` - Keep-alive\n- `busy` - Worker overloaded\n\n**Orchestrator → Worker**:\n- `ack` - Acknowledge handshake\n- `assign` - Send execution + environment\n- `cancel` - Cancel execution\n- `shutdown` - Graceful shutdown\n- `heartbeat` - Keep-alive\n\n#### Message Validation:\n- Runtime validators: `validateWorkerMessage()`, `validateOrchestratorMessage()`\n- Parsers: `parseWorkerMessage()`, `parseOrchestratorMessage()`\n- Serializer: `serializeMessage()`\n\n#### Phase Timings (in ExecComplete):\n- `sandboxSetupMs`\n- `credentialInjectionMs`\n- `proxyStartupMs` (nullable)\n- `cliRuntimeMs`\n- `cleanupMs`\n\n### 7. Table Registry & Retention\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`\n\n#### Lifecycle Classification:\n\n**Metrizable Tables**:\n- Before purge, numeric columns are aggregated into summary metrics\n- Example: `persona_executions` → aggregates `cost_usd`, `duration_ms`, `input_tokens`, `output_tokens` into `daily_metrics`\n\n**Ephemeral Tables**:\n- Rows simply deleted after retention window\n- Example: `persona_events`, `audit_events` (90-day min retention)\n\n#### Registry:\n- Single source of truth for retention policies\n- Prevents hard-coded lifecycle decisions in procedural code\n\n### 8. Configuration\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n\n#### Key Configs:\n- **Auth**: masterKey, claudeToken, teamApiKey, workerToken, supabaseJwtSecret\n- **Network**: wsPort, httpPort\n- **TLS**: tlsEnabled, tlsCertPath, tlsKeyPath, tlsRequireClientCert\n- **Database**: auditDbPath, retentionDays, metricsRetentionDays\n- **Kafka**: kafkaBrokers, kafkaUsername, kafkaPassword (optional)\n- **Queue Backpressure**: maxQueueDepth, perTenantQueueQuota, queueRetryAfterSeconds\n- **Worker Verification**: allowedImageDigests, rejectUnverifiedWorkers\n- **Audit**: auditRetentionDays, auditDbPath\n- **Output Scrubbing**: scrubberEnabled\n\n### 9. Audit Logging & History\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts`\n\n#### Features:\n\n**Hash-Chained Audit Trail**:\n- Every audit entry commits to chain history via SHA-256\n- Previous hash stored in `prev_hash` column\n- Genesis hash: `'0'.repeat(64)` for chain initialization\n- Breaks detectable: if rows purged, next row's hash won't match\n\n**Audit Entry Types** (discriminated union):\n- Key management: `key:encrypt`, `key:decrypt`, `key:decrypt_failed`, `key:delete`, `key:access`, `key:derive`\n- Personas: `persona:create`, `persona:delete`\n- Tools: `tool:link`, `tool-definition:create`\n- Credentials: `credential:link`\n- Subscriptions: `subscription:create`, `subscription:update`, `subscription:delete`\n- Workers: `worker:connected`, `worker:disconnected`\n- **Triggers**: `trigger:create`, `trigger:update`, `trigger:delete`\n- Events: `event:publish`, `event:update`\n- Executions: `execution:submit`\n- Webhooks: `webhook:receive`\n- OAuth: `oauth:authorize`, `oauth:exchange`, `oauth:refresh`, `oauth:refresh_failed`, `oauth:disconnect`\n- Tokens: `token:inject`, `token:expiring_soon`\n\n**Buffered Writes**:\n- In-memory buffer (50 entries or 100ms flush interval)\n- Batched transaction insert for single fsync\n- Automatic flush on buffer overflow\n\n**Query Interface**:\n- `query()` - Filter by tenant, action, actor, resource, timestamp range\n- `stats()` - Aggregations by action, tenant, actor + trend buckets\n- `verify()` - Hash chain integrity check\n- `purgeOlderThan()` - Chunked deletion to avoid blocking\n\n#### Schema:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE audit_events (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,\n  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tenant_id TEXT,\n  actor TEXT,\n  resource_type TEXT,\n  resource_id TEXT,\n  detail TEXT,\n  ip_address TEXT,\n  prev_hash TEXT\n);\n```\n\n#### Indexes:\n- `idx_audit_ts` - Timestamp\n- `idx_audit_tenant_action_ts` - Tenant + action + time (for dashboards)\n- `idx_audit_actor` - Actor tracking\n- `idx_audit_resource_type` - Resource filtering\n\n### Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **Heap-Driven Scheduling**: Eliminates full table scans on every tick; uses min-heap for O(log n) fire time selection\n2. **Tenant Isolation**: Per-tenant DBs with system registry for multi-tenancy at orchestrator layer\n3. **Event-Driven Architecture**: Triggers publish events that subscriptions can listen to; enables event chaining\n4. **Audit-as-Security-Control**: Hash-chained immutable audit trail; every action logged with IP/actor/resource\n5. **Backpressure Handling**: Queue depth limits + per-tenant quotas prevent resource exhaustion\n6. **Graceful Degradation**: Retention engine aggregates metrics before purging; audit chain breakable but detectable\n7. **Type Safety**: Discriminated unions (TriggerConfig, AuditEntry) for compile-time exhaustiveness; runtime validators for protocol messages\n\n### Relevant File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHttpHandlers.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/index.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/triggers.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/events.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/_helpers.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a879324dc3b733e01 (use SendMessage with to: 'a879324dc3b733e01' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74412\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 63206</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9fe338af-0a15-4609-9054-9655c25cf426","uuid":"795360ac-567d-417f-aaf6-a8be4440fe4b","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:45:43.782Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The project structure (packages, key files)\n2. How triggers work - find triggerScheduler, fireDueEntries, and related trigger logic\n3. How the database layer works (look at db.ts, db/ directory, any migrations or table definitions)\n4. How HTTP API routes are defined (httpApi.ts, any route handlers)\n5. How the shared types are defined (types.ts, protocol.ts)\n6. Any existing history or audit logging patterns\n\nFocus on:\n- packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts\n- packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts\n- packages/orchestrator/src/db/ directory\n- packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHttpHandlers.ts\n- packages/shared/src/types.ts\n- packages/shared/src/protocol.ts\n- packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts\n- packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts\n- packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts\n\nRead the full content of each of these files.","agentId":"a879324dc3b733e01","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Project Structure\n\nThe personas-cloud repository is organized as a monorepo with three main packages:\n\n- **packages/shared** - Shared types, protocols, and utilities\n- **packages/orchestrator** - Central service coordinating personas, events, and triggers\n- **packages/worker** - Worker nodes executing persona prompts\n- **Root** - Standard monorepo config with npm workspaces\n\n### 2. Trigger System Architecture\n\nThe trigger system follows a **heap-driven scheduler pattern** with in-memory optimization:\n\n#### Key Files:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts` - Main scheduler\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/triggers.ts` - Trigger persistence\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHttpHandlers.ts` - HTTP API handling\n\n#### How Triggers Work:\n\n1. **Startup** (`buildHeap` function):\n   - `startTriggerScheduler()` loads all enabled triggers from all tenant DBs\n   - Populates an in-memory min-heap keyed by `nextTriggerAt` timestamp\n   - Enables O(1) peek for next due trigger\n\n2. **Scheduled Firing** (`tick` function):\n   - Min-delay: 100ms, Max-delay: 60s\n   - On each tick, heap pops due entries (where `nextTriggerAt ≤ now`)\n   - Counts \"missed\" triggers (> 60s late) for observability\n   - Calls `fireDueEntries()` to process them\n\n3. **Fire Process** (`fireDueEntries` function):\n   - Groups due triggers by tenant ID for efficient batch DB queries\n   - Fetches triggers + persona data via `getTriggersByIdsWithPersona()`\n   - Skips triggers for deleted/disabled personas\n   - Publishes `trigger_fired` event via `publishEvent()`\n   - Computes next fire time: `computeNextTriggerAtFromParsed()`\n   - Updates DB with `updateTriggerTimings()` (last_triggered_at, next_trigger_at)\n   - Pushes updated entry back into heap\n   - Logs firing with metrics\n\n4. **Heap Management** (TriggerSchedulerHandle):\n   - `heapPush()` - Add/update trigger in heap\n   - `heapRemove()` - Remove trigger from heap\n   - `nudge()` - Force immediate re-evaluation\n   - `getMetrics()` - Return scheduler observability data\n\n#### Trigger Types (from types.ts):\n- `'manual'` - No automatic firing\n- `'schedule'` - Cron or interval-based (supported: `\"every Xm/h/s/d\"` shorthand or standard cron)\n- `'polling'` - Poll URL at interval\n- `'webhook'` - Receive external triggers\n- `'chain'` - Triggered by events from other personas\n\n### 3. Database Layer\n\n#### Architecture:\n- **Single-database mode** (legacy): Monolithic SQLite with all tenants\n- **Multi-tenant mode** (current): System DB + per-tenant DBs via `TenantDbManager`\n\n#### Key Database Files:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` - Schema definitions\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/index.ts` - Barrel export\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/_helpers.ts` - Utilities (stmt cache, row mappers)\n\n#### Core Tables:\n- `personas` - Persona definitions\n- `persona_triggers` - Trigger definitions (indexed on enabled + next_trigger_at)\n- `persona_events` - Event queue (status: pending, processing, delivered, skipped, failed, partial, partial-retry)\n- `persona_event_subscriptions` - Event listener subscriptions\n- `persona_executions` - Execution history and results\n- `persona_tool_definitions` - Tool definitions\n- `persona_credentials` - Encrypted credentials\n- `inference_profiles` - Model/provider configurations\n\n#### Key Features:\n- **WAL mode** enabled for concurrency\n- **Foreign key constraints** enforced\n- **Prepared statement caching** via `stmt()` helper\n- **Automatic migrations** for schema evolution\n- **Row mapper factory** for type-safe mapping\n\n### 4. HTTP API Routes\n\n#### Files:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` - Main HTTP server\n\n#### Route Structure:\n- **Exact-path routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:/path`)\n  - OAuth, token, status, execute, admin routes\n  - Delegated to specialized handlers\n\n- **Resource routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]`)\n  - Personas CRUD + sub-resources (tools, credentials, subscriptions, triggers)\n  - Events CRUD + webhooks\n  - Subscriptions, Credentials, Executions, Tool-definitions\n\n#### Trigger Routes (via `triggerHttpHandlers.ts`):\n- `POST /api/triggers` - Create trigger → `heapPush()` + `nudge()`\n- `PUT /api/triggers/:id` - Update trigger → update DB + update/remove from heap\n- `DELETE /api/triggers/:id` - Delete trigger → `heapRemove()` + delete DB\n- `GET /api/personas/:id/triggers` - List triggers for persona\n\n#### Key Design Patterns:\n- Route parsing: `/api/{resource}[/{id}[/{subResource}]]`\n- Auth context extraction: admin vs user-scoped access\n- Database routing via `TenantDbManager` for multi-tenant\n- Error handling: 400 (validation), 404 (not found), 409 (conflict), 429 (backpressure), 500 (internal)\n\n### 5. Shared Types\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n\n#### Core Domain Types:\n\n**Persona**:\n- `id`, `projectId`, `name`, `description`, `systemPrompt`\n- `enabled`, `maxConcurrent`, `timeoutMs`\n- `inferenceProfileId`, `networkPolicy`, `maxBudgetUsd`, `maxTurns`\n\n**Events**:\n- `PersonaEvent` - Event record with status state machine\n- Event statuses: `'pending' | 'processing' | 'delivered' | 'skipped' | 'failed' | 'partial' | 'partial-retry'`\n- Legal transitions defined in `EVENT_TRANSITIONS` map\n- `PersonaEventSubscription` - Listener binding persona to event types\n\n**Triggers**:\n- `PersonaTrigger` - Trigger record (id, personaId, triggerType, config, enabled, nextTriggerAt)\n- `TriggerConfig` - Discriminated union of config types\n- `TriggerType` - `'manual' | 'schedule' | 'polling' | 'webhook' | 'chain'`\n\n**Execution**:\n- `PersonaExecution` - Execution record (id, personaId, status, inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd)\n- `ExecRequest` - Request to execute persona\n- `ExecResult` - Completion result\n\n**Credentials**:\n- `PersonaCredential` - Encrypted credential storage (encryptedData, iv, tag)\n- `InferenceProfile` - Model provider configuration\n\n### 6. Protocol Definitions\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts`\n\n#### WebSocket Protocol (dac-wire):\n\n**Worker → Orchestrator**:\n- `hello` - Initial handshake with capabilities\n- `ready` - Worker ready to accept assignments\n- `stdout` / `stderr` - Output chunks\n- `complete` - Execution finished\n- `event` - Custom event emission\n- `progress` - Phase progress (0-100%)\n- `heartbeat` - Keep-alive\n- `busy` - Worker overloaded\n\n**Orchestrator → Worker**:\n- `ack` - Acknowledge handshake\n- `assign` - Send execution + environment\n- `cancel` - Cancel execution\n- `shutdown` - Graceful shutdown\n- `heartbeat` - Keep-alive\n\n#### Message Validation:\n- Runtime validators: `validateWorkerMessage()`, `validateOrchestratorMessage()`\n- Parsers: `parseWorkerMessage()`, `parseOrchestratorMessage()`\n- Serializer: `serializeMessage()`\n\n#### Phase Timings (in ExecComplete):\n- `sandboxSetupMs`\n- `credentialInjectionMs`\n- `proxyStartupMs` (nullable)\n- `cliRuntimeMs`\n- `cleanupMs`\n\n### 7. Table Registry & Retention\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`\n\n#### Lifecycle Classification:\n\n**Metrizable Tables**:\n- Before purge, numeric columns are aggregated into summary metrics\n- Example: `persona_executions` → aggregates `cost_usd`, `duration_ms`, `input_tokens`, `output_tokens` into `daily_metrics`\n\n**Ephemeral Tables**:\n- Rows simply deleted after retention window\n- Example: `persona_events`, `audit_events` (90-day min retention)\n\n#### Registry:\n- Single source of truth for retention policies\n- Prevents hard-coded lifecycle decisions in procedural code\n\n### 8. Configuration\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n\n#### Key Configs:\n- **Auth**: masterKey, claudeToken, teamApiKey, workerToken, supabaseJwtSecret\n- **Network**: wsPort, httpPort\n- **TLS**: tlsEnabled, tlsCertPath, tlsKeyPath, tlsRequireClientCert\n- **Database**: auditDbPath, retentionDays, metricsRetentionDays\n- **Kafka**: kafkaBrokers, kafkaUsername, kafkaPassword (optional)\n- **Queue Backpressure**: maxQueueDepth, perTenantQueueQuota, queueRetryAfterSeconds\n- **Worker Verification**: allowedImageDigests, rejectUnverifiedWorkers\n- **Audit**: auditRetentionDays, auditDbPath\n- **Output Scrubbing**: scrubberEnabled\n\n### 9. Audit Logging & History\n\n#### File:\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts`\n\n#### Features:\n\n**Hash-Chained Audit Trail**:\n- Every audit entry commits to chain history via SHA-256\n- Previous hash stored in `prev_hash` column\n- Genesis hash: `'0'.repeat(64)` for chain initialization\n- Breaks detectable: if rows purged, next row's hash won't match\n\n**Audit Entry Types** (discriminated union):\n- Key management: `key:encrypt`, `key:decrypt`, `key:decrypt_failed`, `key:delete`, `key:access`, `key:derive`\n- Personas: `persona:create`, `persona:delete`\n- Tools: `tool:link`, `tool-definition:create`\n- Credentials: `credential:link`\n- Subscriptions: `subscription:create`, `subscription:update`, `subscription:delete`\n- Workers: `worker:connected`, `worker:disconnected`\n- **Triggers**: `trigger:create`, `trigger:update`, `trigger:delete`\n- Events: `event:publish`, `event:update`\n- Executions: `execution:submit`\n- Webhooks: `webhook:receive`\n- OAuth: `oauth:authorize`, `oauth:exchange`, `oauth:refresh`, `oauth:refresh_failed`, `oauth:disconnect`\n- Tokens: `token:inject`, `token:expiring_soon`\n\n**Buffered Writes**:\n- In-memory buffer (50 entries or 100ms flush interval)\n- Batched transaction insert for single fsync\n- Automatic flush on buffer overflow\n\n**Query Interface**:\n- `query()` - Filter by tenant, action, actor, resource, timestamp range\n- `stats()` - Aggregations by action, tenant, actor + trend buckets\n- `verify()` - Hash chain integrity check\n- `purgeOlderThan()` - Chunked deletion to avoid blocking\n\n#### Schema:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE audit_events (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,\n  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tenant_id TEXT,\n  actor TEXT,\n  resource_type TEXT,\n  resource_id TEXT,\n  detail TEXT,\n  ip_address TEXT,\n  prev_hash TEXT\n);\n```\n\n#### Indexes:\n- `idx_audit_ts` - Timestamp\n- `idx_audit_tenant_action_ts` - Tenant + action + time (for dashboards)\n- `idx_audit_actor` - Actor tracking\n- `idx_audit_resource_type` - Resource filtering\n\n### Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **Heap-Driven Scheduling**: Eliminates full table scans on every tick; uses min-heap for O(log n) fire time selection\n2. **Tenant Isolation**: Per-tenant DBs with system registry for multi-tenancy at orchestrator layer\n3. **Event-Driven Architecture**: Triggers publish events that subscriptions can listen to; enables event chaining\n4. **Audit-as-Security-Control**: Hash-chained immutable audit trail; every action logged with IP/actor/resource\n5. **Backpressure Handling**: Queue depth limits + per-tenant quotas prevent resource exhaustion\n6. **Graceful Degradation**: Retention engine aggregates metrics before purging; audit chain breakable but detectable\n7. **Type Safety**: Discriminated unions (TriggerConfig, AuditEntry) for compile-time exhaustiveness; runtime validators for protocol messages\n\n### Relevant File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHttpHandlers.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/index.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/triggers.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/events.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/_helpers.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/protocol.ts`\n- `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`"}],"totalDurationMs":63206,"totalTokens":74412,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":806,"cache_read_input_tokens":69731,"output_tokens":3870,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":806},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
